name: M Mac
text:
I bought this strawberry drink because I was curious about it. Sad to say, I will not be buying it again because I think the owner(s) failed to realize that drinks containing REAL MILK have to be refrigerated. I popped this drink open, took my first sip, and got a mouth full of sour strawberry milk. 🤢

Mind you, this drink and many others like it, were not refrigerated when I bought. I only realized that after I tried to drink the beverage. This is a warning to anyone who buys this type of drink. If it has milk in it and it is not refrigerated, DO NOT BUY IT!

Otherwise, the store is nice and they have a decent selection of international foods.

I prefer to shop at local, small markets, so I checked out this place when I first moved into the area.  Attracted to the pick 5 meat deal, I picked a variety of packs.  I'm a huge carnivore, adore all things meat, but I did something with the five packs of meat I've NEVER done with meat - I threw it all out!

The bacon is, I suspect, boar bacon rather than pork...obnoxious odor and flavor evident as soon as it hit the pan.  Similar experience with the pork steak, and the beef was so tough even after slow simmering for hours it was inedible.  Crucial telling point: one of my cats will eat ANY meat and beg for more and she refused any scrap from this haul.  That's when I just tossed it all.  A failed experiment.  I wanted to like this place, to support someone stuck right next to a big box, trying to make it, but no.  Just...no.

name: Brian Swan
text:
Holiday International Market is easily the best store in the Huntsville area for Korean groceries. If you are cooking Korean cuisine, then this is the store to visit, as they will likely carry most of the ingredients that you will not be able to get at a standard supermarket.

Some outstanding products available at Holiday International Market include:

- A variety of kimchi, both fresh and fermented
- Mandu (Korean dumplings)
- Banchan (side-dishes), such as seaweed salad and spicy fish-cakes
- Ready-to-cook marinated beef and pork
- Asian pear

They also carry a great selection of Korean cookware, utensils, and dinnerware. The staff is very friendly and welcoming. I highly recommend visiting this store if you have any interest in Asian and especially Korean food.
